-- MOVES-RBC Global Asset Management appoints CEO of int'l business
-- 
-- Wed Aug 20, 2014 05:14AM EDT
-- None



Aug 20 (Reuters) - RBC Global Asset Management, a unit of Royal Bank of Canada <RY.TO>, appointed Clive Brown as CEO and managing director of its international business.

Brown joins from JP Morgan Asset Management, where he was the global chief operating officer and chairman of Asia, based in Hong Kong. He will take charge on Oct. 1 and will be based out of London. He will report to John Montalbano, chief executive of RBC GAM.